{
  "texts": [
    "Neural prosthetics is a category of human-machine interfaces that aim to replace motor, sensory, or cognitive impairments due to injury or disease.",
    "Among them, the most advanced are currently visual and cochlear implants.",
    "Cochlear implants are surgically implanted neural prosthetic devices able to restore the loss of hearing functions by stimulating spiral ganglion nerves.",
    "The implant consists of an array of electrodes implanted along the cochlea such that each section stimulates a region corresponding to a specific frequency 175.",
    "Most control strategies are based on amplitude modulation of a biphasic current pulse train 176."
  ]
}